        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 5:43PM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 543 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lolita, or 10 miles southeast of Edna, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ganado, La Ward, Lolita, Blessing, Vanderbilt, Lake Texana Dam,
Midfield, and Louise.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
